The paper deals with a multi-agent system and its control, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of consensus tracking algorithm and event triggered control mechanism suggests the paper could also belong to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of sliding mode control and its robustness makes it relevant to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of nonlinear control, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
